description:
MACHINERY (drain recovery gap, witnessed live flow-mmh3 this drain): a /flow <key> --auto run that DIES mid-pipeline BEFORE opening a PR (zombie/crash/OOM during plan or implement) strands its bead IN_PROGRESS plus an orphaned worktree, with NO auto-recovery path:
- the drain loop reads action=done (the dead run lease goes non-live, so evolve_select sees no blocking run), so the loop terminates as if the backlog drained, but the bead never shipped;
- the sonnet escalation ladder (verb-evolve C) cannot see it (bd ready EXCLUDES in_progress beads; the ladder only catches DNFs that leave the bead OPEN);
- A2 evolve_session_cleanup skips it (its stoppable gate requires a TERMINAL bead closed/blocked/deferred; an in_progress bead is treated as maybe-still-working);
- evolve_reap is PR-only (a pre-PR death has no green leaf PR to reap).
Net: the bead sits IN_PROGRESS, invisible to every drain channel, until a human notices. Witness: flow-mmh3 attempt 1 (job 08d4ea06) zombied deep in implement (staged deletions, never committed or PR-d); the drain read done with mmh3 unshipped; only caught by manual inspection.

SECONDARY (recovery anti-pattern, witnessed attempt 2): a do-resume into the DIRTY worktree of attempt 1 (staged file deletions in the index plus state.json implement:in_progress) RE-DIES at implement entry, because records_diff_baseline --capture-blobs runs against planned files already deleted-in-worktree-but-present-in-HEAD. Correct recovery: tear down the dirty worktree, reopen the bead, fresh /flow <key> --auto off origin/main (clean index), NOT a do-resume. Fresh attempt (job 0015776c) shipped cleanly (PR-324), proving mmh3 was never the problem.

FIX SKETCH: add a drain detection (extend evolve_session_cleanup or a new evolve_reap-adjacent check) for a STRANDED pre-PR dead run = bead IN_PROGRESS AND lease non-live AND no open/merged PR for its branch; recovery = reap the worktree plus reopen the bead (in_progress to open) so the next drain turn relaunches it FRESH (never do-resume the dirty worktree). Gate done-termination on this too: the loop should not read done while a stranded in_progress + nonlive + noPR bead exists. Evidence: verb-evolve drain (done-termination gate, A2 terminal-bead gate, C ladder bd-ready scope); evolve_session_cleanup.py stoppable gate; evolve_reap.py (PR-only). NOT hot (no guard file).
